            <div class="row text-left">
              <div class="col-xs-12">
                <h4 class="text-left">User stories:</h4>
                <ol>
                  <li>I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: <kbd>January 1, 2016</kbd>)</li>
                  <li>If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.</li>
                  <li>If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.</li>
                </ol>

                <h4 class="text-left">Example usage:</h4>
                <a href="https://timestampms-joey.herokuapp.com/April%2007,%201990" target="_blank"><code>https://timestampms-joey.herokuapp.com/April%2007,%201990</code></a><span>Click for try</span><br>
